6ljUX07ZEX0z-m8WGvjULwekKZDrgeny1-Vf97WrKpVoNa0htHg=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering property settings**\\n\\nI think we already used javac in the scratch earlier, and I'm wondering if that's okay. Now, maybe it isn't. I'm pondering whether the `java.vendor` property in the native image is read-only, which could affect things. Should I try using `System.setProperty`? Hmm, I'm just not completely sure about that. I’ll need to check the documentation or test it to confirm if it works without issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JUnit extension issues**\\n\\nI'm considering that entering `canLoad` is fine, which is a relief. However, if there are existing tests in the JVM using an IBM Java vendor that can trigger a KerberosError during `canLoad`, that might lead to some exception handling. I'm also thinking that the JUnit extension may need to autoload some resources that aren't within the native scope. It seems like that's not an issue to worry about anymore. I’ll finalize my answer on that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added an early JUnit extension so the Kafka test JVM sets `java.vendor` to an IBM-like value before any test can initialize `KerberosError`.\n\nNew files:\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/KerberosVendorExtension.java`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/resources/junit-platform.properties`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/services/org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.Extension`\n\nWhy this helps:\n\n- The remaining uncovered call site is inside `KerberosError.canLoad(...)`, which only runs when `Java.isIbmJdk()` returns `true`.\n- Setting `java.vendor` inside the individual `KerberosError` test was too late if another test initialized `KerberosError` first.\n- The auto-detected JUnit extension sets the property before each test class, and also from its static initializer when the extension is loaded, increasing the chance that the first `KerberosError` initialization takes the IBM branch and reaches `Class.forName(...)` in `canLoad`.\n\nI did not run the Gradle tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_001d093e6ef2bd43016a0f394033108195995159fadfcc574c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1084, "output": 1351, "cacheRead": 48128, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50563, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779382573537, "responseId": "resp_001d093e6ef2bd43016a0f392e4a3881958ad6490307f14b14"}}
