egister(\"kerberosVendorAgentJar\", Jar) {\n    archiveClassifier = \"kerberos-vendor-agent\"\n    from sourceSets.test.output\n    manifest {\n        attributes \"Premain-Class\": \"org_apache_kafka.kafka_clients.KerberosVendorAgent\"\n    }\n}\n\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    dependsOn kerberosVendorAgentJar\n    systemProperty \"java.vendor\", \"IBM Corporation\"\n    jvmArgs \"--add-exports=java.security.jgss/sun.security.krb5=ALL-UNNAMED\"\n    doFirst {\n        jvmArgs \"-javaagent:${kerberosVendorAgentJar.get().archiveFile.get().asFile.absolutePath}\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWhy this should cover the remaining call site:\n\n- `KerberosError.canLoad(...)` only executes from the enum static initializer when `Java.isIbmJdk()` sees `java.vendor` containing `IBM`.\n- Setting the property inside the `KerberosError` test method or via a JUnit extension can be too late if another Kafka test initializes `KerberosError` first.\n- A premain agent runs before the test framework loads/discovers tests, so the first `KerberosError` initialization should take the IBM branch and execute the `Class.forName(...)` call inside `canLoad(...)`.\n\nI did not run the Gradle tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_001d093e6ef2bd43016a0f3a2dbfd081958325f00f311fc0f1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2432, "output": 924, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53020, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779382813843, "responseId": "resp_001d093e6ef2bd43016a0f3a1e736881958e02048f895716b0"}, "toolResults": []}
